'''Toyohira Shrine''' (豊平神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Toyohira-ku, Sapporo]], [[Hokkaido]], Japan. Its former shrine Rank under the [[modern shrine Ranking system]] was ''Gōsha'' (郷社).
== Enshrined Deities == The shrine enshrines the following deities: ; {{ill|Kamitsukeno no Tamichi|ja|上毛野田道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno no Tamichi|qq=}} (上毛野田道命) : The main deity. Worship began when [[Abe Nitaro]], a settler from Aomori, enshrined a deity from [[Saruka Shrine]] in his homeland. ; [[Ōyamatsumi]] (大山祇神) : The mountain deity. It was enshrined to honor the forestry activities during the settlement period. ; [[Ukanomitama no Kami]] (倉稲魂命) : The deity of agriculture. Enshrined to support the settlers' agricultural endeavors.
== History == * [[:en:1871|1871]] (Meiji 4) – [[Abe Nitaro]] constructed a small shrine to enshrine Kamitsukeno Tamichi no Mikoto. * [[:en:1884|1884]] (Meiji 17) – Construction of a new shrine building. * [[:en:1889|1889]] (Meiji 22) – Official recognition as a public shrine. * [[1919]] (Taisho 8) – Designated as a ''sonsha'' (village shrine). * [[1943]] (Showa 18) – Elevated to ''gōsha'' status.
== Stone Monuments == ; Monument to Nitaro Abe : Erected on July 3, [[:en:1899|1899]] (Meiji 32), it is said to be the oldest surviving monument in Toyohira Ward. ; Manchuria War Dead Memorial Monument : Erected in [[:en:1906|1906]] (Meiji 39) to honor those from Toyohira Village who perished in the [[Russo-Japanese War]]. ; Irrigation Union "Meritorious Names" Monument : Erected on September 1, [[1914]] (Taisho 3), located in the shrine's courtyard, it commemorates those who contributed to the establishment of irrigation for Toyohira and neighboring villages. ; 50th Anniversary of the Irrigation Union Monument : Erected on September 1, [[1943]] (Showa 18), inscribed with the name of then-Mayor [[Shoji Hashimoto]] of Sapporo.
